<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[192,1440,419,572]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,348,419,443]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Comments.</emphasis>
Specimens were collected during April, May, August, and September from litter under rhododendron, damp litter at the bottom of an incline, and from moss on a log.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[192,1440,419,572]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferro &amp; Carlton" authorityYear="2010" box="[240,534,483,507]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sonoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasstownensis">
<emphasis box="[240,534,483,507]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Sonoma brasstownensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has aedeagal characters unlike any other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1886" box="[1051,1151,484,507]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sonoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1051,1151,484,507]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Sonoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The apically expanded lamina of the distal 1/3 of the endophallus will serve to distinguish this species from all others in the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
